    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="383"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 24, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You may acknowledge tender of Mora settlement when conveyed to you by minister
                    for foreign affairs in answer to your note of 18th June, by accepting the
                    payment to the United States, on or before 15th next September, of $1,500,000 in
                    Spanish gold pesos in full discharge and satisfaction not only of the principal
                    sum agreed to be paid in liquidation of the Mora claim so called, but of any and
                    every amount that might be claimed to be due as interest on said principal sum.
                    I add for your information that in a note dated August 13 minister of Spain
                    describes the stipulated gold pesos as being current money in the Island of
                    Cuba. Should minister for foreign affairs use the same phrase you will treat it
                    as explanatory and merely emphasizing the pledge to pay in pesos and in gold,
                    but not importing any increased difference between value of American and Spanish
                    gold nor indicative of any purpose to make payment in Cuba.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
